logs.transcript: Thank you for calling Meeker County Court Administration. Our office hours are 8 a.m. until 4.30 p.m. Monday through Friday. If you know the extension of the party you are calling, you may dial it at any time. If you are calling to pay or have questions regarding a transfer citation, please press 1. You will be directed to the Minnesota Court Payment Center. If you are calling to find out if you need to report for jury duty, please press 2. This is a recorded line only and does not connect you to a live person. If you are calling for the recorder's, assessor's, public defender's, or county attorney's offices, please hang up and dial those offices directly as we are not able to transfer. For questions regarding probate matters including guardianship, conservatorship, estates, and civil commitments, press 3. For questions regarding family matters including dissolution, custody, adoptions, child protection, and orders for protection, press 4. For questions regarding civil matters including harassment, restraining orders, evictions, conciliation, and judgments, press 5. For all other questions, including jury, press 6. To repeat this message, press the star key. For judgments, name changes, minor statements, and other information, please press 5.
